1. e4
{ All the lines are based on extensive and careful analysis as well as grandmaster and correspondence play. We consulted all the major sources  (books, DVDs etc.)  and found a lot of improvements  (in some cases even refutations)  .  Here is the list of the sources where we checked what other authors recommend for White.  Books:  Martyn Kravtsiv - “The Italian Renaissance”  (Quality Chess 2020)   Larry Kaufman - “Kaufman's New Repertoire for Black and White”  (New In Chess 2019)   Milos Pavlovic - “The Modernized Scotch Game”  (Thinkers Publishing 2019)   Alexander Khalifman and Sergei Soloviov - “Squeezing 1.e4 e5: a Solid Strategic Approach”  (chess-stars 2019)   Alexander Delchev - “Bc4 against the Open Games”  (New In Chess 2018)   Christof Sielecki - “Keep it Simple 1.e4”  (chessable/New In Chess 2018)   John Shaw - “Playing 1.e4. Caro-Kann, 1...e5 and Minor Lines”  (Quality Chess 2016)   Karsten Muller & Georgios Souleidis - 'Winning with the Slow  (but Venomous!)  Italian'  (New In Chess 2016)   Yelena Dembo & Richard Palliser - “The Scotch Game”  (Everymanchess 2011)   John Emms - “Beating 1e4 e5”  (Everyman 2010)   Vladimir Barsky - “The Scotch Game for White”  (Chess Stars 2009)   D.Taylor & K.Hayward - 'Play the Ponziani'  (Everymanchess 2009)   Jan Piński - “Italian Game and Evans Gambit”  (Everymanchess 2005)   Alexander Khalifman - “Opening for White According to Anand vol. 1”  (Chess Stars 2003)   Joshua Doknjas - "Opening Repertoire: The Ruy Lopez"  (Everymanchess 2019)   Videos/DVDs:  Fabiano Caruana - “Navigating the Ruy Lopez”  (Chessbase DVD)   Parimarjan Negi - “The Modern Scotch Opening”  (Chessbase DVD)   Ivan Saric - “A new look at the Italian  (Giuoco Piano)  ”  (chess24)   Sergei Tiviakov - “The Bishop’s Opening and The Italian Game”  (ChessBase DVD)   Nigel Davies - “Attack with The Modern Italian”  (ChessBase DVD)   Simon Williams - “Rocket Repertoire: The Four Knights”  (ChessBase DVD)   Simon Williams - “Evans Gambit for the new generation”  (ChessBase DVD) }
