{ This is the main position of the Rio de Janeiro Variation, which has been established as White's best chance for an advantage. White has numerous tries here and before examining them, it is important to understand the general features of the position. In my view, the key to its understanding lies in realization that Black's light square bishop is the most important piece on the board. While temporarily buried on c8, it has the potential to become a powerful piece, if developed along the b1-h7 or h1-a8 diagonal. If Black deploys it comfortably, in conjunction with putting his knight on an excellent e6 square, his pieces will enjoy remarkable harmony and he will hardly ever be worse. On the contrary, he will acquire great chances of taking over the initiative. If, however, White succeeds in restricting its development, he will be able to develop play against Black's structural weaknesses and force him to passive defence.    Having understood this, it is easy to predict both sides' plans. Black will try to play ...d5 with further ...Bf5 or ...Bb7 and .. .c5 on the cards. White's main idea will be to deny his opponent this possibility and he has 3 main ways to do so: early Re1, intending exd6 after .. .d5, forcing an undesirable ...Bxd6 due to an attack on the e7 bishop; early Nd4, putting c6 under attack; or early c4, intending to take control of the d5 square with Nc3 and Rd1. However, I believe Black has enough resources to meet any of these plans and achieve a fair share of chances. Enough of this lengthy introduction, let's study concrete variations! }
9. Be3 O-O 10. Re1
{ A flexible way of playing. White does not commit to c4 or Nc3 yet. } 10... d5
11. c4
{ White uses the fact that he has not commited the knight to c3 to undermine Black's centre. }
11... f5
{ Black takes active counteraction.   It is of key importance to remember this move, which is better than schematic play with  11...Nc5 }
12. Nc3 f4 13. Bd2 d4 14. Ne4 c5
{ The protected passed pawn and great light-square play give Black the more comfortable game. }
*

