9. Nd4
{ The centralized knight stops ...d5 as our pawn on c6 would be undefended. }
9... O-O 10. Nc3 Bc5
{ The key move. Black intends ... Re8, ... Bxd4 and ...d5, achieving comfortable play. }
11. Rd1 Re8 12. Qh5 { The most straightforward try. } 12... Bxd4 13. Rxd4
{ White wants to play 14.Rh4, hoping for a quick rout of Black's position. However, an unpleasant surprise awaits him. }
13... d5 14. Rh4
{ In view of Black's next move, this is a clear mistake. But the other moves obviously do not cause Black any discomfort either. }
14... Bf5
{ Like a bolt from the blue! This tactical trick refutes White's conception. He can't take the bishop because of ... Qxh4 and White finds himself in dire straits. Both c2 and e5 pawns are hanging. Black is close to winning. }
