{ We exchange our strong bishop but in return we remove White's strong knight and we can finally play ...d5 next. Otherwise it would be difficult to develop. }
13. Rxd4 d5 14. Ne4
{ This move, using the pin to reroute the knight to a better position, has been played most often in this position. It may be best but it still does not pose Black any real problems. }
14... Qe7 15. Ng3 Nc5
{ White's dark square control is compensated by Black's light square control. }
*

