21. b4
{ White hopes to create a grip and if Black exchanges White will make a good use of the a-file. }
21... d5
{ It is desirable to build up our position in the centre so we should always consider this move in this structure. }
22. Nc5 Bxc5
{ We can't tolerate such a knight. We are going for the opposite coloured bishops when it's not entirely clear which bishop is better. }
23. Bxc5
{ The engine likes  23.bxc5  but then we also play  23...Ba6  or even  23...Bd7  with ...Be8-g6. }
23... Ba6
{ The position is balanced. In some cases after ...Bc4 we may consider sacrificing a pawn with ...d4 and with ... Bd5 we may build a nice attack. }
