{ A strong temporary pawn sacrifice. } 9. Nxe5 d5
{ Opening the position and taking advantage of the lack of harmony between the white pieces.   White can't hold on to his extra pawn here. }
10. Bf4 c6 { Pushing the bishop back to a worse square. } 11. Ba4 dxe4 12. dxe4
Qxd1 { 12...Nxe4  13.Qxd8  Bxd8  is also possible, with equality. } 13. Raxd1
Nxe4 *

