{ White plans to play Nc4 to chase away the bishop from the optimal diagonal. }
8... c6 9. Ba4 d6 10. Bc2
{ Completely non-critical. Black can pretty much play as he pleases. Wesley So chose an ambitious plan and gained an upper hand against Fabiano Caruana. }
10... Be6 11. Qe2
{ 11.Kh1?  would be a blunder in view of  11...Ng4!  and 12...Qh4. } 11... h6
12. Kh1 g5 { Black prevents f4 once and for all. } 13. Nc4 Bc7 14. Ne3 d5
{ Black is going to castle long and will have promising play in the centre and on the kingside. }
15. Re1 Qe7 16. a4 O-O-O 17. Rb1 d4 18. Nf1
{ This was Caruana-So, Norway Chess 2018 Now after } 18... g4
{ Black would be much better. } *

