17. Qxh6 Bb6+ 18. d4 Rg4
{ 18...Rg6  19.Qh8+  Ke7  20.Qh4+  would lead to a draw, but Black can play for more. }
19. Qh8+ Ke7 20. Qf6+ Kd7 21. Qxf7+ Qe7 22. axb3 c5
{ Black's king is surprisingly safe and he is the side who can play for the win. A sample line goes: }
23. Be3 cxd4 24. Bxd4 Bxd4+ 25. cxd4 Qxf7 26. Rxf7+ Kc6
{ Black has good chances to get into rook&bishop vs rook endgame, which he can try to win. }
