{ The Knight temporarily blocks the bishop but we will maneuver it to e6 or g6. }
7. Nbd2 O-O 8. Nc4 Re8 9. Be3 Bd6
{ Many other moves are possible, but this is the most straightforward one. Black's idea is to play ... Nf8-g6, stopping White's typical ideas on the kingside: Nh4-f5 and f4-f5. White has failed to demonstrate any downsides to this idea in practical play. }
10. a4
{ Getting some space on the queenside but we just continue with our usual maneuver. }
10... Nf8 11. a5 Ng6 12. Kh1 f6
{ 12...Be6?!  right away would be less accurate in view of  13.Ng5! } 13. Ng1
Be6 14. Ne2 Qd7 15. Qd2 Bf8
{ Before playing the desired ...b5, Black retreats the bishop in order for it not to be exchanged for the c4-knight. }
16. b3 b5 17. axb6 axb6
{ White has not achieved anything in Karjakin-Sasikiran, Qatar 2015. Black has a comfortable game. }
*

