1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4
{ The Scotch Game had always remained in the shadow of the Ruy Lopez and the Italian Game, until Garry Kasparov started playing it successfully in the 1990s. Since then, many players have decided to follow the world champion's example and nowadays it is a popular opening on both professional and amateur level. }
3... exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 { The main and most reliable move. } 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. Bd3
d5 7. exd5
{ This is harmless and fortunately it doesn't kill the game. The positions are equal but we can find some imbalance and play for a win. }
7... cxd5 8. O-O Be7 9. c4 d4
{ 9...O-O  10.cxd5  Bb7  11.Nc3  Nxd5  is fine if you are happy with a draw. The position is just dry. With our move we try to play for more. }
10. Bg5 O-O 11. Nd2 a5
{ A nice move, preventing any expansion on the queenside with b4. In addition, in some lines ...Ra6 might be an idea. }
