{ 9...d6  should equalize comfortably but this is more ambitious.  It's a generally useful move preparing ...Ba6 in some lines and ...a4 in case of b3. This wasn't considered in Milos Pavlovic's book 'The Modernized Scotch Game'  (Thinkers Publishing 2019) }
10. c4 Nb6
{ Now we have a position from the 8.c4 Nb6 9. Nd2 variation with the moves h4 and a5 included, which rather benefits Black, if anyone. }
