{ Once the f4 square is available, Black should use it! We are fighting for more than equality. Milos Pavlovic in his book 'The Modernized Scotch Game' @@StartBracket@@Thinkers Publishing 2019@@EndBracket@@ considers only   9...Ba6  when  10.Nf3  Qb4  11.Kd1  is another story and probably less good for us. }
10. Qe3 Bh6
{ It looks as if something has gone wrong for White, but he has a cunning idea in mind. By the way, the less complicated option is  10...Ne6  , with a good position, if you don't want to memorize too much lines. }
11. Kd1 { Stepping out of ...Nxg2+ } 11... O-O
{ Going for it! Now White can win some material and the game is really becoming wild. If you want to be a strong player you shouldn't be afraid to play principled moves if you can get the advantage. Still, you can have a look at  11...d5  provided in this chapter as an alternative. }
