15. Qxe5
{ This seems to be the lesser evil, although White is still walking a tightrope. }
15... Qb4 16. Qc3 Qd6
{ Black's attack plays itself. The following line is not necessary to remember, but it demonstrates that White remains worse even after perfect defence. }
17. Be2 Bf5 18. Ke1 Bg7 19. c5 Qd7 20. Qa3 Re8 21. Nf1 Bd3 22. Ne3 Bxe2 23.
Kxe2 Qg4+ 24. Kf1 Qf3 25. Rg1 Rad8 26. Qa6 Rd4 27. Qe2 Qh3+ 28. Ke1 Rxf4 29. h5
Qh2 30. Rf1 f5 31. hxg6 hxg6 32. Bd2 Rfe4 33. Rc1 f4 34. Rc4 fxe3 35. Rxe4 Rxe4
36. Bxe3 Bxb2
{ At the end of this long computer line, the worst is over for White, but he still has to defend an endgame, a pawn down. }
