21. Ne7+
{ A forcing continuation which is just bad for White and it's nice to see how well Black is doing in the endgame. You can pause learning this line if it's too much, it's not very likely to happen and these kinds of things you can work out over the board. }
21... Kh8 22. Bxa8 Rxa8 23. b4 Bxe5
{ Black is winning but please check this line carefully. } 24. Nc6
{ 24.Bf4  Bb2  25.Bxc7  Na4  White has no defense against c3-c2. } 24... Bf5
25. Nxe5 Bxb1 26. Bxa3 Bxa2 27. Bb2 f6
{ With a clear pawn to the good and a strong passer, Black should win. } *

