6. O-O { This natural move doesn't meet demands of the position. } 6... a5
{ Black begins chasing the bishop, facing White with very difficult problems. This is a very strong move but it was played only once in OTB games. }
7. Bb3 d6 8. h3 Be7
{ An immediate  8...b5  is not as precise, because after  9.a3  Nxb3  10.cxb3  White can play  d4  next in one go.  However, Black's position is still perfectly fine - it actually transposes to 5.0-0 with 6.Bc4 line. It's just that with the text Black strives for more than equality. }
9. d3 b5 10. a3 Nxb3 11. cxb3 O-O
{ Black is for choice thanks to the bishop pair and the better structure. } *

