7. a3 Bc5
{ 7...b5  is possible  but once we trade on b3 White's plan is to push d4 so it's better to wait for d3 and win a tempo this way. }
8. Nxe5 { This pawn is not hanging because of } 8... d6 9. Nd3 Bg4 10. Qe1
{ 10.f3  is just unplayable as there comes the devastating  10...Nxf3+  when neither piece can be taken because it's double check, and ideas of a  ...Nxh2  discovery are coming. }
10... Ba7 { White is lost because his pieces are disastrously misplaced, e.g. }
11. e5 O-O { and the rook is coming to the e-file. } *

