{ The recent correspondence and over the board praxis has established this move to be very promising, yielding Black great results. As we will see, White can easily end up in trouble if he does not proceed cautiously. }
5. Ba4 c6
{ A little but very powerful move. Black may play some ...b5, ...a5 chasing the bishop but the main point is revealed when White accepts the gambit and takes on e5.   The two times more popular  5...Bc5  is playable but  6.Nxe5  O-O  7.Nd3  Bb6  8.e5  Ne8  9.Nd5  doesn't seem to be so convincing for Black. }
