1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6
{ In this chapter we will focus on 4.Bc4 but we will also have a look at some lesser known moves such as even 4.a3 and 4.a4. }
4. d3 { Just too passive to be good. It's funny that it's worse than 4.a4. }
4... d5 { We obviously grab the centre. } 5. exd5 Nxd5 6. Nxd5 Qxd5 7. Be2 Bf5
{ Going for the long castle is the maximalist option. Sample line goes: } 8.
O-O O-O-O 9. Be3 f6 10. a3 Kb8 11. b4 g5
{ The opposite flank attacks have similar pace, but in addition Black has the better control over the centre. }
