11. O-O Rf8 { Black is much better. Possible lines are: } 12. f4
{ 12.Bd5  Bb6  13.Kh1  d6  ... Bxf2 and ...Ng4 are decisive threats  14.f4  Nxd5  15.exd5  Qe2  16.Nd2  Bg4  -+  Black will play ... Rae8 and ... Kd8, whereas White has no way to untangle his pieces. }
12... Qxe4 13. Bc4 d6 14. Kh1 Bd7 15. Nd2 Qc6 16. Re1+ Kd8
{ White has little compensation for the pawn. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
