1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6
{ In this chapter we will focus on early gambits starting from this position. }
3. d4
{ This position is covered in the chapters about the Scotch, but here we will have a look at some Gambit tries. }
3... exd4 4. c3 { A Goring Gambit. } 4... d5
{ A simple way to avoid any gambits and achieve a comfortable position.  4...dxc3  5.Bc4  cxb2  6.Bxb2  is really interesting but it's not practical to go into something so complex when we don't have to. }
5. exd5 Qxd5 6. cxd4 Bg4 { We have a very easy development. } 7. Be2
{ 7.Nc3  Bb4  8.Be2  transposes. } 7... Bb4+ 8. Nc3 Bxf3
{ Very concrete, we have 9...Qc4 in mind. The idea is that in the endgame we will play against the isolated d-pawn. }
9. Bxf3 Qc4 { The queen is very annoying on c4 stopping White from castling. }
10. Bxc6+ bxc6 11. Qe2+ Qxe2+ 12. Kxe2 O-O-O
{ Both sides have pawn weaknesses, objectively the position is equal. } 13. Be3
Ne7 *

