1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6
{ In this chapter we will focus on early gambits starting from this position. }
3. Nc3 Nf6
{ This is the Four Knights but here we will look at the Belgrade and Halloween Gambits. }
4. d4 exd4 5. Nd5
{ The Belgrade Gambit, which is one of the weirdest opening ideas I have seen- what are the benefits of plonking the knight on d5? I found a great antidote to this line. }
5... Nb4
{ A very concrete reply, which promises Black a slight edge in many lines. } 6.
Bc4 { Everything gets semi forced for many moves now. } 6... Nbxd5 7. exd5 Bb4+
8. Bd2 Qe7+ 9. Qe2 Bxd2+ 10. Kxd2 Qxe2+ 11. Kxe2 c5
{ A nice way of forcing 12.dxc6 as otherwise White's structure would be bad  @@StartBracket@@weak d5 pawn@@EndBracket@@. }
12. dxc6 bxc6 13. Nxd4 d5 14. Bd3 c5 15. Nb5 Kd7
{ Black will put the king on c6 and his hanging pawns will rather be a strength than a weakness. }
*

