5... Bxd4 6. Nxd4 Nxd4 7. Bg5 h6 8. Bh4
{ It is important not to fall into White's trap:  8...g5?  9.f4! } 8... d6 9.
f4 Bg4 { Black initiates a forcing sequence. } 10. Qd2 g5
{ A strong move which wasn't tried in OTB games. } 11. fxe5
{ Obviously  11.fxg5  is met by  11...Nxe4 } 11... dxe5 12. Bg3 Qe7
{ Black is very solid and although White's compensation is enough to regain the pawn he is not able to equalize. Sample line is: }
13. Nc3 O-O-O 14. Qf2 Qc5 15. Bxf7 Nh5 16. Bxh5 Bxh5 17. Kh1 Rhf8 18. Qg1 Bf7
{ Black's more active pieces give him a slight edge. } *

