11... Nc6 { Attacking the weak d4-point. } 12. Nd5 Be7 13. hxg5 Bg4
{ The bishop was unstable on h5. } 14. Rg1 Be6 15. Nf6+ Bxf6 16. exf6 Bxc4
{ The only, but perfectly good move. } 17. fxg7 Rg8 18. Bxf4 Rxg7
{ 18...Qe7+  19.Kf2  O-O-O  is also possible, but I prefer keeping the king on the kingside, where it is more safe. }
19. Kf2 Bd5
{ The bishop assumes a powerful central position. The opposite-coloured bishops improve Black's attacking chances. }
20. Qe2+ Kf8
