[Black "Bishop's Opening 4.Qe2"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Bc4
{ The Bishop's Opening has recently been gaining in popularity, mainly as a means of avoiding the Petroff Defence. }
2... Nf6 3. d3 c6
{ I believe Black should take the opportunity to grab space in the centre. This way, he can fight for more than equality. }
4. Qe2 { A choice of dubious value. } 4... Bc5 5. Nf3 O-O 6. O-O
{ After  6.Bg5  d6  the bishop is not great on g5. Black can easily unpin with ...Nbd7.   And of course  6.Nxe5?  d5!  7.Bb3  Re8  is bad for White. }
6... d5 7. Bb3 h6
{ If White does nothing, Black continues with ... Re8 and the queen on e2 is really not feeling well. Therefore the critical continuation is: }
8. exd5 cxd5 9. Qxe5 { But after } 9... Nc6 10. Qg3 Bd6 11. Qh4 Ne7
{ the white queen is feeling badly. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
