[Round "?"]
[White "27. Bishop's Opening (2.Bc4)"]
[Black "Bishop's Opening 4.Nf3 #01"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Bc4
{ The Bishop's Opening has recently been gaining in popularity, mainly as a means of avoiding the Petroff Defence. }
2... Nf6 3. d3 c6
{ I believe Black should take the opportunity to grab space in the centre. This way, he can fight for more than equality. }
4. Nf3 d5 5. Bb3 a5 { Softening up the bishop on b3. } 6. a3
{ In this way, White surrenders even more space, which already gives Black reasonable hopes of achieving an opening advantage. }
6... a4 7. Ba2 Bd6 8. Nc3 d4
{ We can't keep d5 but let's just grab even more space. } 9. Ne2 c5 10. Ng3 O-O
11. O-O Nc6
{ Black has more space on the queenside and in the centre, so all that is left for White is to try and attack on the kingside. However, Black can easily repel this attack, and achieve the better chances, e. g. }
12. h3 h6 13. Nh4 Re8 14. Nhf5 Bf8 15. Nh5 Nxh5 16. Qxh5 Be6 17. Bxe6 Rxe6 18.
f4 g6 19. Qg4 Qe8
{ White's attack has reached a dead end. Black is ready to develop the queenside initiative. }
*

