1. e4 e5 2. Bc4
{ The Bishop Opening has recently been gaining in popularity, mainly as a means of avoiding the Petroff Defence. }
2... Nf6 3. d4
{ The rare Urusov Gambit, which we forgot to even include in the beta version. It was pointed out by one of the testers. Fortunately, Black doesn't face too many problems here. }
3... exd4 4. Nf3 Bb4+
{ A strong disruptive check, using the lack of castle on White's part. } 5. c3
dxc3 6. bxc3 d5 { Giving back the pawn to speed up the development. } 7. exd5
Be7 { The easiest choice, not allowing Qe2+. } 8. O-O O-O 9. Bb3
{ Positionally forced, as ...c6, destroying White's structure, was threatened. Now it would be well met by c4. }
9... Bg4 10. c4 Ne4 { A very important resource. The threat is ...Bf6. } 11.
Nbd2 Ng5 { This permanent pin is very unpleasant for White. } *

