[White "29. Centre Game (2.d4) & Others"]
[Black "Centre Game 4.Qc4 #01"]
[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. Qxd4
{ Centre Game is a strange opening choice. White loses an important tempo in the opening and develops his pieces awkwardly. Black can successfully fight for more than equality. }
3... Nc6 4. Qc4
{ This is much less known than  4.Qe3  but it's not without its points. } 4...
Nf6 5. Nc3 Bb4 { Just developing actively. } 6. Bd2 O-O 7. O-O-O a5
{ This is more accurate than natural  7...Re8  8.f3   We need to act quickly, otherwise White can create an unpleasant bind with f3 and g4. With our move we protect the bishop and prepare ...Ne5 ...Re8 and ...d5. }
8. a3 Bxc3 9. Bxc3 b5
{ Of course we need to play vigorously once we gave up the bishop pair. } *

