1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. Qxd4
{ Centre Game is a strange opening choice. White loses an important tempo in the opening and develops his pieces awkwardly. Black can successfully fight for more than equality. }
3... Nc6 4. Qe3 Nf6 5. Nc3 Bb4 { Just developing actively. } 6. Bd2 O-O 7.
O-O-O Re8 8. Qg3
{ White gets out of the pin and if he manages to play f3 his position is actually quite nice. We have to accept the sacrifice. }
8... Nxe4 9. Nxe4 Rxe4 10. Bf4 Qf6
{ A powerful move.  10...d6  11.Bd3  gives White a nice development. } 11. Nh3
{ The point was  11.Bxc7  d6  12.Bxd6  Qh6+  . } 11... d6 12. Bd3 Nd4
{ A sharp tactical battle begins. } 13. Kb1 Ne2 14. Qf3 Ba3
{ Using weak squares around White's king and the momentum perfectly! } 15. Bc1
Qxf3 16. gxf3 Re7 *

